{{Infobox airport | name = Bétou Airport | nativename = | nativename-a = | nativename-r = | image = | image-width = <!-- if less than 200 --> | caption = | image2 = | image2-width = <!-- if less than 200 --> | caption2 = | IATA = BTB | ICAO = FCOT | FAA = | TC = | LID = | GPS = | WMO = | type = Public | owner-oper = | owner = | operator = | city-served = [[Bétou]], [[Republic of Congo]] | location = | hub = | built = <!-- military airports --> | used = <!-- military airports --> | commander = <!-- military airports --> | occupants = <!-- military airports --> | metric-elev = | elevation-f = 1168 | elevation-m = | coordinates = {{coord|3|03|28|N|18|30|55|E|type:airport_region:CG|display=inline,title}} | website = | image_map = | image_mapsize = | image_map_alt = | image_map_caption = | pushpin_map = Republic of the Congo | pushpin_label_position = | pushpin_label = '''BTB''' | pushpin_map_alt = | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_image = | pushpin_map_caption = Location in the Republic of the Congo | r1-number = 08/26 | r1-length-f = | r1-length-m = 1000 | r1-surface = Dirt | metric-rwy = y | footnotes = Source: GCM<ref name="GCM">{{GCM|BTB|Bétou Airport}}</ref> Google Maps<ref>[https://www.google.com/maps/@3.057639,18.5154421,1998m/data=!3m1!1e3 Google Maps - Bétou]</ref> }}
'''Bétou Airport''' {{airport codes|BTB|FCOT}} is an airport within the town of [[Bétou]] in the [[Likouala Department]], [[Republic of the Congo]]. The runway also serves as part of the road leading westward out of town.
Bétou is on the [[Ubangi River]], the border with the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]]. East approach and departure will cross the river into the DRC.
