The '''Copernicus Atmosphere Monitoring Service (CAMS)''' is part of the [[Copernicus Programme]] and provides continuous data and information on atmospheric composition. The service describes the current situation, forecasts the situation a few days ahead, and analyses consistently retrospective data records for recent years. This service has around 10 years of developments, and its current precursor project, MACC-III (Monitoring Atmospheric Composition and Climate - Interim Implementation), is delivering the pre-operational Copernicus Atmosphere Service. The service is being implemented by the [[European Centre for Medium-Range Weather Forecasts]] (ECMWF).<ref>[http://www.ecmwf.int/en/about/media-centre/news/2014/copernicus-climate-change-and-atmosphere-monitoring-services Copernicus Climate Change and Atmosphere Monitoring Services launched]</ref>

