{{Infobox building | name = Sammarinese Museum of Ancient Arms | image = La Cesta o Fratta of San Marino.jpg | building_type = [[Military]] | architectural_style = | structural_system = | location = [[San Marino]] | completion_date = 1956 | architect = | structural_engineer = | services_engineer = }}
'''Sammarinese Museum of Ancient Arms''' (''Museo delle armi antiche di San Marino'' in Italian) is located in the Cesta, the [[The Three Towers of San Marino|second tower]] of [[San Marino]]. The museum opened in 1956 due to agreement with Sammarinese collector Giovanni Carlo Giorgetti. Exhibition, divided to four rooms, contains about 2000 [[List of ancient weapons|ancient arms]] and [[armour]]s. It is part of the [[Musei di Stato]].
==External links== *{{Official website|http://www.museidistato.sm/Museo_trad/mtc/2torre_2museo-armi-antiche.htm}}
