{{Infobox political party |country = Andorra |name = Social Democracy and Progress |native_name = Socialdemocràcia i Progrés |colorcode = #CD1B68 |logo = File:Social Democracy and Progress Andorra logo.jpg |leader = Víctor Naudi Zamora |split = |foundation = May 2013 |ideology = [[Social democracy]]<ref name="Nordsieck">{{Cite web|url=http://parties-and-elections.eu/andorra.html|title=Andorra|last=Nordsieck|first=Wolfram|date=2015|website=Parties and Elections in Europe|access-date=9 April 2018}}</ref> |position = [[Centre-left]] |headquarters = [[Andorra la Vella]] |colours = |members = |european = |international = |seats1_title = [[General Council (Andorra)|General Council]] |seats1 = {{Composition bar|2|28|hex=#CD1B68}} |website = [http://www.sdpand.com/ sdpand.com] }} {{Politics of Andorra}} '''Social Democracy and Progress''' ({{lang-ca|Socialdemocràcia i Progrés}}, SDP) is a political party in [[Andorra]] led by [[Víctor Naudi Zamora]].
==History== Established in May 2013,<ref>[http://www.parties-and-elections.eu/andorra.html Andorra] Parties and Elections in Europe</ref> the PSD ran in the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 2015|2015 parliamentary elections]]. In the constituency elections the party received 9% of the vote and failed to win a seat. However, it also received 11% of the [[proportional representation]] vote, winning two seats.<ref>[http://www.ipu.org/parline-e/reports/2005_E.htm Last elections] IPU</ref>
