{{notability|date=May 2017}}
[[File:The Natashas Project.png|thumb|The Natashas Project logo]]
'''The Natashas Project''' is a [[modern dance]] company that aims to increase awareness of [[modern slavery]] and [[human trafficking]] in the United Kingdom and internationally.<ref>[https://www.itc-arts.org/members-directory/the-natashas-project The Natashas Project.] Independent Theatre Council. Retrieved 24 May 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.berkhamstedtoday.co.uk/news/contemporary-dance-show-in-hemel-hempstead-will-raise-awareness-of-sex-slavery-1-5946598 Contemporary dance show in Hemel Hempstead will raise awareness of sex slavery.] ''Berkhamsted & Tring Gazette'', 19 March 2014. Retrieved 24 May 2017.</ref> It was founded in 2012 by [[Erena Bordon Sanchez]]<ref>[http://harrietparkerbeldeau.co.uk/projects/the-natashas-project/ The Natashas Project.] Harriet Parker-Beldeau. Retrieved 24 May 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.rudemagazine.co.uk/culture/the-natashas-project.php The Natashas Project.] ''Rude'', 12 November 2015. Retrieved 24 May 2017.</ref> and receives funding from the [[Arts Council England]].

